title.narrative: Equitable access to quality education opportunities provided

description.narrative: UNICEF supported 1,689,888 conflict-affected children with learning opportunities. Specifically, UNICEF:Rehabilitated and furnished ;90 schools affected by the conflict.Provided nonformal education services to 45,886 OOSC with 21 implementing partners across 13 governorates.Delivered critical messages to123,288children and caregivers through Back to Learning Community Outreach Campaigns.Distributed 901,000 national textbooks, 127,100 Curriculum B textbooks to children attending formal schools, and 200,771sets of SLM to OOSC in NE Syria.Additionally, UNICEF supported the Education-Sector-led operationalization of accommodation centres for crossline and cross-border children participating in the national exams. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:16/01/2022
